711356f-a.text:
New York Hospital, 6-12 West 16th Street, south side, just west of Fifth Avenue. This institution was chartered in 1771, and admitted its first patient in 1791. The original buildings were demolished in 1869, and the 15th to 16th Streets buildings opened in 1877. They will be demolished in 1934, when the hospital moves to York Avenue. For further views see 15th Street adjoining N.W. corner of Fifth Avenue.
The gray buildings in the background are St. Francis Xavier College and Church.
About 1927.

Ewing Galloway.

711358f-b.text: West 16th Street, south side, west of Fifth Ave. Shown is the gate of the former New York Hospital. View No. 2 is of the clearance. Both are in a southward direction. An apartment house will improve the site. March 22, 1935
